Police in Kisumu have dismissed claims of the re-emergence of gangs that have been terrorising residents The an incident in which a group of armed youths attacked and critically injured a man in Nyalenda estate on Friday. Locals claim a 30 member- gang armed with iron bars and knives carried out a door-to-door raid in search of rivals before they accosted one of their rivals whom they critically injured. The victim suff ered serious panga wounds on his arms and legs and is admitted at one of the hospitals in Kisumu. Locals who sought anonymity said some of the attackers are former members of the 40 brothers’ gang. But Kisumu OCPD Christopher Mutune denied the claims of the reemergence of gangs.